{
  "text": "Measurements of vertebral aBMD are usually limited to AP projections. However, in this scanning modality, the results could possibly be influenced by the posterior vertebrae elements, aortic calcifications, and osteoarthritis of the spine seen in the majority of elderly patients [CITATION_1] . These confounding elements can be excluded or reduced when using LAT scanning. A number of studies using estimation of aBMD based on LAT DXA have shown a stronger relationship with vertebral fracture frequency, ultimate load, or the age of patients compared to aBMD from AP projections [CITATION_2] .",
